page.title: 139 th May at St Catherine'S
page.content: The morning was misty and damp. I nearly forgot my netball stuff for the match we were playing against Lifton.In school we went into Mr Greenacre's assembly. It was about Jesus and his disciples. After that we did Oxford English one of my favourite subjects. At dinnertime I was on dinner rota that means cutting up the dinner for the younger children. After dinner, on the field we had fun but it is more fun when we play on the bars. After playtime we watched a quick television programme before the match.. It was about nature.When we had changed for the match we made our way to the cars and went to Lifton.At the end of our game the score was 10 - ! We had won and I had scored 8 of the goals. Our second team won scoring 14 - 0. They were thrilled.
